By the Quene. Where of late tyme there hath ben a certayne staye and intermission of the auncient free entercourse for marchaundise, betwixt this realme and the lowe countreys belongyng to the Kyng of Spayne the Quenes Maiesties good brother ... Proclamations. 1564-12-29 England and Wales. Sovereign (1558-1603 : Elizabeth I)
1 sheet ([1] p.)
in Powles Churchyarde, by Rycharde Jugge and John Cawood: printers to the Quenes Maiestie, Imprinted at London : [1564]
A proclamation restoring intercourse of merchandise with the Low Countries. Title from caption and first lines of text. Dated at end of text: Yeven at her hyghnes palaice of Westminster, the. xxix. of December, in the seuenth yere of her Maiesties raigne, 1564. At foot of sheet: Cum priuilegio Regiæ Maiestatis. Reproduction of original in the Folger Shakespeare Library.
